\#\#\# \*\*Expected GPT Response Format:\*\*  
\`\`\`  
Your revenue model is 70% recurring ($70K MRR, $30K project revenue), creating baseline predictability while maintaining flexibility for larger project premiums. With 12 active clients averaging $8,333/month (calculated ACV), you're operating in the mid-market tier — past SMB volume requirements but not yet enterprise coordination complexity.

Your 2.5% monthly churn (roughly 30% annual turnover) means you're replacing approximately a third of your client base each year. This translates to an implied replacement rate of 2.5% monthly growth just to stay neutral — before accounting for any net expansion. Your 40-month average client lifetime validates this churn rate, indicating most relationships last 3+ years.

Concentration Risk: MEDIUM — your top 5 clients represent 65% of revenue (top 10 at 80%). While not critically concentrated, losing any large relationship would create meaningful impact, particularly given your 1.3-month cash runway from Financial tab. This suggests building reserves or diversifying your client base alongside retention focus.

Your typical win rate of 40% exceeds industry benchmarks of 30-35%, suggesting effective qualification and proposal quality. Combined with your primarily referral-driven acquisition (ranked 1st, with partnerships 2nd and content 3rd), this indicates strong client satisfaction driving growth — though reliance on referrals limits your ability to control acquisition timing without developing more proactive systems.

Overall Client Model: Mid-market, relationship-intensive operation with strong retention foundation and effective sales conversion, tempered by moderate concentration risk and referral-dependent acquisition.  
\`\`\`

